MM8D - Growing house controlling and remote monitoring device
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

1. About software
-----------------
  It is an internal software for MM8D controlling and monitoring device.
You can view actual status with a browser application and administrate it
with SSH client.
  This software originally made to Raspberry Pi, but you can install on
Debian GNU/Linux on PC, too.

Requirements:

  Hardware: Raspberry Pi 3 Model B.
  Software: Raspbian OS Lite,
            Apache webserver,
            GNUPlot,
            Perl,
            Python3.

  Hardware: PC with a paralel port.
  Software: Debian GNU/Linux operation system,
            Apache webserver,
            GNUPlot,
            Perl,
            Python3.

2. How to get installer package for my OS?
------------------------------------------
a. Visit homepage (see later) to download installer packages:

  Raspbian OS:      mm8d-sw-0.2-armhf.tar.gz

                    mm8d-eec_0.2-1_armhf.deb
                    mm8d-sw_0.2-1_armhf.deb
                    mm8d-web_0.2-1_all.deb

  Debian GNU/Linux: mm8d-sw-0.2-i386.tar.gz
                    mm8d-sw-0.2-x86_64.tar.gz

                    mm8d-eec_0.2-1_i386.deb
                    mm8d-sw_0.2-1_i386.deb
                    mm8d-eec_0.2-1_x86_64.deb
                    mm8d-sw_0.2-1_x86_64.deb
                    mm8d-web_0.2-1_all.deb

b. Download from Github

  $ git clone https://github.com/pozsarzs/mm8d-sw.git

c. Download from Debian repository

  set reporitory:
  $ sudo echo "deb http://www.szerafingomba.hu/deb/ ./" >> /etc/apt/sources.list
  $ sudo wget -q -O - http://www.szerafingomba.hu/deb/KEY.gpg | apt-key add -
  $ sudo apt-get update

  install:
  $ sudo apt-get install mm8d-sw mm8d-eec mm8d-web

